Tony,<br><br>
When enough of us become politically active and kick ass in Washington, there may well be hope sometime down the road. Unfortunately, too many people are so egocentric that they cannot see reality beyond the surface of their skin, and they ignore the problems of society that do not directly impact their daily mud bath.<br><br>
The sense of self and the sense of society have become separated. Therein, I believe, lies some of the problem. Too much appearances and keeping up with the neighbors, and pushing responsibilities for real problems upon others who do not exist, but they like to think exist. These people were born shallow, live shallow, and will die shallow. Thankfully, they can afford deep graves.<br><br>
I share your sense of frustration. As a Vietnam Veteran, I have seen some of the worst, and some of the best, and I also know a little of what it means &quot;to sit at the back of the bus.&quot; I can only hope that we realistically can land somewhere on the better side of the middle! <br><br>
